His defense already lost one of his best pass rushers, defensive end Osi Umenyiora, to free agency and now faces the reality that Pierre-Paul is no lock to be recovered from back surgery in time for opening day. Some of that is offset by the return of Mathias Kiwanuka to defensive end, but that move leaves Fewell without all three of his starting linebackers from last year.
